div.p:
The Secretary: They may be but we have seen several reports to the contrary;
                    involving military operations on the ground in Angola, which roads the
                    Portuguese advise the MPLA to take, etc.

Mr. Hyland: A good many of them have yet
                    to be gotten out. Let’s remember that November 11 is the date for independence;
                    the date for Portuguese withdrawal is not until February.
